programme.title: Kidsongs: Play Along Songs
programme.desc: Come and play along with the Kidsongs Kids and their wacky music teacher, Professor Majorchord. This video's made to get kids up and moving so jump right in! Songs include: Fooba Wooba John, Three Little Fishes, Down by the Station and more!

programme.title: Paulie
programme.desc: When a bird sets out to find the girl who raised him, he discovers his way with words can get him into trouble. But as fast as he can talk himself into a fix, his odd menagerie of human friends can help him realize all he wants is to be home!

programme.title: Mike the Knight and the Journey to Dragon Mountain
programme.desc: When Mike's Dad, the King sets off on a mission, Mike is determined to follow him!

programme.title: Alpha And Omega: Family Vacation
programme.desc: Pack up for a howling fun movie adventure filled with action, laughs, and tender moments as Kate and Humphrey take their pups on their first family vacation!\n\nTV-G.

programme.title: Paulie
programme.desc: When a bird sets out to find the girl who raised him, he discovers his way with words can get him into trouble. But as fast as he can talk himself into a fix, his odd menagerie of human friends can help him realize all he wants is to be home!

programme.title: Kidsongs: My Favorite Songs
programme.desc: When Billy Biggle lands in the Kidsongs Kids’ backyard, it’s sure to be a fun-filled day! Watch these songs with Billy and Ruby and they’ll be your favorites, too. Songs include: Old MacDonald Had a Farm, Five Little Monkeys, BINGO and more!

programme.title: Kidsongs: Let's Put on a Show
programme.desc: When the Kidsongs Kids put on a show, catchy tunes, great costumes, and wonderful songs make this a video you'll want to watch over and over again! Songs include: It's Magic, Me and My Shadow, Mr. Bass Man, Blue Suede Shoes and more!

programme.title: Kidsongs: If We Could Talk To Animals
programme.desc: The Kidsongs Kids learn to chat in chimpanzee and discuss in rhinoceros! This wonderful animal adventure will keep you singing and laughing along! Songs include: Hound Dog, Talk to the Animals, Five Little Monkeys, The Old Hen and more!

programme.title: Kidsongs: I'd Like to Teach The World To Sing
programme.desc: Join the Kidsongs Kids and their tour guide, Mr. World, as they visit different countries of the globe and meet the kids of other lands. Songs include: I'd Like to Teach the World to Sing, Kumbaya, London Bridge, Frere Jacques and more!

programme.title: Kidsongs: I Can Do It
programme.desc: Join the Biggles and the Kidsongs Kids as they explore all the things they know how to do, like build sandcastles, get soaked bathing adorable puppies, ride bikes and fly kites. Songs include: I Can Do It, All Shook Up, Peanut Butter and more!

programme.title: Kidsongs: I Can Dance
programme.desc: The Kidsongs Kids and the Biggles will have you doing the Charleston, the Twist, the Waltz and Barefootin' at the beach. Songs include: I Can Dance, Twist and Shout, Mexican Hat Dance, Mashed Potato Time and more!

programme.title: Kidsongs: Good Night, Sleep Tight
programme.desc: This video is designed to help kids transition from an active day to bedtime with great music, and a little help from our Sandmen. Songs include: Hush Little Baby, Lullaby and Good Night, The Unicorn, Pat-A-Cake and more!

programme.title: Kidsongs: Country Sing Along
programme.desc: We're going to the country! You'll be stompin' your feet and clappin' your hands every time you watch this country music video fun-fest. Songs include: Swingin', Achy Breaky Heart, Buffalo Gals, On the Road Again, Born to Be a Cowboy and more!

programme.title: Kidsongs: Cars, Boats, Trains and Planes
programme.desc: If you love things that go, you’ll love this video! Join the fun as the Kidsongs Kids sing along aboard all kinds of trucks, a boat and even a bulldozer. Songs include: Car Car Song, Row, Row, Row Your Boat, The Bus Song and more!

programme.title: Kidsongs: Boppin' with the Biggles
programme.desc: Join the Kidsongs Kids, put on your dancin' shoes and let's go Boppin' with the Biggles! Songs include: Walkin' the Dog, Head, Shoulders, Knees and Toes, La Bamba, Loco-Motion, Little Red Caboose and more!

programme.title: Kidsongs: Adventures In Biggleland: Meet the Biggles
programme.desc: You'll have lots of laughs when Billy and Ruby Biggle introduce you to the zany residents of Biggletown. Songs include: Consider Yourself, Alouette, The Muffin Man, Ta-Ta-Ra Boom-Dee-A, Let's Rock It Up and more.

programme.title: Kidsongs: A Day with the Animals
programme.desc: Lots of animal friends co-star with the Kidsongs Kids in this magical journey throughout the animal kingdom. Songs include: BINGO, Do Your Ears Hang Low?, Itsy Bitsy Spider, How Much is That Doggie in the Window and more!

programme.title: Hugo
programme.desc: Set in 1930s Paris, an orphan who lives in the walls of a train station is wrapped up in a mystery involving his late father and an automaton.

programme.title: Funpak: Maximmoblie / Audit of Evil / Belt for Punichment / Serentiy Now
programme.desc: Trevor and Eric take the Maximmobile out for a spin. / Harold is looking forward to a vacation. / The Koalas are challenged to a wrestling match. / Mr. Titis day off is interrupted.

programme.title: Funpak: Fishy Memories / Jazz Matazz / Secret Lair / Bad Dream Machine
programme.desc: Bernard remembers his childhood. / Coolman is sick of hearing the same old songs. / Eric and Trevor try to get satellite TV. / Octofreak had invented a nightmare machine.

programme.title: Funpak: Candy Bandit / Ledger Lad / Doomsday Dog / Night at the Office
programme.desc: Someone is stealing candy from babies. / Harold is trying to capture the X of Evil. / Maxter XOX wants to be an evil mastermind. / Clark overhears a conversation and jumps to conclusions.

programme.title: MST3K Shorts
programme.desc: Friendly Patrolman Hal Jackson visits the Dixon family to instruct their youngest son, Alan, in the art of safe and courteous driving.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: Secret Agent Super Dragon
programme.desc: A secret agent tries to stop a drug lord from taking over the world with hallucinogenic chewing gum.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: Untamed Youth
programme.desc: Joel invents a pipe with a smoke detector and a sprinkler system built in for the invention exchange. The guys watch a 1950s teen flick about youths sentenced to manual labor at a cotton farm.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: Mitchell
programme.desc: The trio sit through a dreary Joe Don Baker disasterpiece as Gypsy tries to find a way to save Joel from being killed by the Mads.

programme.title: MST3K Shorts
programme.desc: Nick wants to take Kay out on a date, but isn't sure what they'd do. The short offers ideas like taffy pulls and scavenger sales. Nothing says romantic quite like a scavenger sale.

programme.title: MST3K Shorts
programme.desc: A high school senior named Sue and her boyfriend want to get married right after Sue graduates. A marriage counselor discourages the young couple from entering into a hasty marriage.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: The Violent Years
programme.desc: Jam Handy shows the world the glory of sexism with electric kitchen appliances and Ed Wood analyzes the world of criminals spoiled by their parents.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: Rocket Attack U.S.A.
programme.desc: The crew watches the second chapter of The Phantom Creeps and a film about an American spy sent to the Soviet Union to investigate a missile attack. Joel hosts a quiz show with the Bots.

programme.title: The New Detectives
programme.desc: It is difficult to convict a murderer if the body can't be found. But forensic science is finding ways to do it. Devious killers can think up many was to dispose of their victim's remains, but they are often no matches for investigators.

programme.title: The New Detectives
programme.desc: Hairs and Fibers: The tiniest filament can become a mark of distinction in the most singular and intimate of ways. Investigators have come to rely on forensic evidence as fine as a carpet fiber or as innocent as an eyelash to crack difficult cases.

programme.title: The New Detectives
programme.desc: Forensic Botany & Geology: Plants help provide oxygen and nutrients for existence. Soil is the fertilizer of life. Yet both can yield clues to the time and location of a person's death.

programme.title: The New Detectives
programme.desc: Toxicology: While drugs can cure disease and ease pain, they can also be agents of murder. Toxicologists can examine blood and tissue to uncover cases where death is not as natural as it may seemfrom slow arsenic poisoning to quick cocaine overdoses.

programme.title: The New Detectives
programme.desc: Tool marking: A tool used to commit a crime can often be the same tool used to solve it. The pattern a machine leaves on an item, the unusual way a tool crimps a wire, and even something as innocuous as the shape of a wood chip can lead to a killer.

programme.title: The New Detectives
programme.desc: New Forensic Techniques used to Solve Old Cases: Advancement in science and technology are encouraging people to revisit the past in hopes of answering questions that have remained unanswered, and solving crimes that seemed unsolvable.

programme.title: The New Detectives
programme.desc: Investigators are always on the cutting edge of new forensic techniques that can help them solve cases more accurately. An experimental brain fingerprinting technique has already won the acquittal of a police officer accused of a drug charge.

programme.title: The New Detectives
programme.desc: Arson Investigation: Insurance torchings, mob burnouts and arson murders: these crimes are designed to take all clues with them. But a solid case can be built from a heap of ashes.

programme.title: The New Detectives
programme.desc: Terrorism: Thanks to new technology and, perhaps, the approaching millennium, terrorism is a growing international threat. The Oklahoma City explosion and the bombing of the World Trade Center are just two of the incidents of this growing problem.

programme.title: The New Detectives
programme.desc: Some people will let nothing stand between them and their goals. In their tortured minds, raw desire replaces all reason, and homicide becomes a convenient means to an end.

programme.title: The New Detectives
programme.desc: Sometimes the scales of justice are balanced by just a few milligrams of evidence  a couple of fibers, a tooth filling, or a smudge on a piece of tape. The biggest cases are often solved by the smallest clues.

programme.title: The New Detectives
programme.desc: George Orwell's concept of Big Brother remains in the realm of fiction. But as technology becomes more a part of our lives, it's becoming increasingly more difficult to make a move without leaving behind an electronic trace.

programme.title: The New Detectives
programme.desc: Hiding a body can be difficult; it's sometimes easier to obscure or disguise the circumstances of the death, turning murder into suicide, or pinning the blame on someone else. The truth is told through subtle clues taken from the crime scene.

programme.title: The New Detectives
programme.desc: No matter how chaotic or how clean a crime scene appears to be, the culprit is bound to leave something telling behind. Occasionally, it's nothing more than a fingerprint or shoe tread. Sometimes that's all that's needed.

programme.title: The New Detectives
programme.desc: Men don't have a monopoly on murder, but it's still extraordinary when women kill. Though female killers are as deadly as males, they choose less violent methods.

programme.title: The New Detectives
programme.desc: For a price, anything's possible. Contract killings arose out of the need to establish the perfect alibi. By hiring someone else to do the dirty work, a person can deflect guilt, at least in theory.

programme.title: The New Detectives

programme.desc: Fue uno de los casos más inusuales en la historia forense. Los investigadores tuvieron que encontrar una manera de resolver un caso de asesinato con una evidencia que consistía en un tomate aplastado encontrado en la escena del crimen.

programme.title: Crímenes imperfectos
programme.desc: Cuando una maestra dedicada y respetada desapareció, la policía tuvo que determinar si se había ido de vacaciones sin decírselo a nadie, o si era víctima de un juego sucio.

programme.title: Crímenes imperfectos
programme.desc: La policía de Seattle no tenía sospechosos en el violento asesinato de la cantante post-grunge, Mia Zapata.

programme.title: Crímenes imperfectos
programme.desc: Un estudiante de posgrado de la Universidad Estatal de Michigan desapareció y se presumió muerto. Con la ayuda de un profesor de ciencias geológicas, la policía esperaba obtener la información de su asesino.

programme.title: Crímenes imperfectos
programme.desc: ¿Qué tan desafortunado puede ser un hombre? Su esposa se quitó la vida y su novia de la universidad se suicidó de la misma manera catorce años antes. Los investigadores tuvieron que determinar si esto era solo una extraña coincidencia o un asesinato.

programme.title: Crímenes imperfectos
programme.desc: En 1996, Gayle Isleib, de 54 años, fue emboscada en su camino de entrada de Manchester, Connecticut, y asesinada a tiros. Ahora la policía debe determinar si el amor se convirtió en obsesión... y en un motivo de asesinato.

programme.title: Crímenes imperfectos
programme.desc: La víctima había sido agredida sexualmente y apuñalada hasta la muerte en la playa. Se descubrió un par de zapatos de tenis de hombre cerca de su cuerpo.

programme.title: Crímenes imperfectos
programme.desc: Una niña de 13 años desapareció de su casa en Colorado y la única evidencia que dejó el secuestrador fueron tres huellas digitales en la pantalla de una ventana.

programme.title: Crímenes imperfectos
programme.desc: Un asesinato brutal, muchos sospechosos y pruebas contradictorias, pero los forenses fueron claros en una cosa: el asesino conocía a su víctima. Y eso les dio a los investigadores una ventaja.

programme.title: Crímenes imperfectos
programme.desc: Un asesino en serie andaba suelto y la policía tenía que encontrarlo antes de que atacara nuevamente. Su pista más prometedora fue inusual: una huella dactilar sangrienta en el cuerpo de una de las víctimas.

programme.title: Crímenes imperfectos
programme.desc: En la noche de Halloween de 2004, Adriane Insogna y Leslie Mazzara fueron brutalmente asesinadas en su casa de Napa, California.

programme.title: Crímenes imperfectos
programme.desc: Después de que el sospechoso fuera declarado culpable de incendio premeditado y asesinato, mantuvo su inocencia pero fue sentenciado a 25 años de prisión.

programme.title: Crímenes imperfectos
programme.desc: Una mujer fue brutalmente asesinada en su casa y los únicos testigos del crimen fueron los perros de la familia.

programme.title: Crímenes imperfectos
programme.desc: El asesino probablemente esperaba cubrir sus huellas escenificando la escena del crimen. Pero los investigadores descubrieron el intento casi de inmediato y recurrieron a la ciencia forense para saber qué sucedió esa noche realmente.

programme.title: Crímenes imperfectos
programme.desc: Una niña de seis años corrió y se escondió cuando vio que su abuela era golpeada hasta la muerte, pero el hombre la siguió, golpeó y agredió. Ella dijo que el agresor era su tío, quien fue condenado. Se retractó de su testimonio años después.

programme.title: Crímenes imperfectos
programme.desc: En 1984, el cuerpo de la universitaria Laura Salmon fue encontrado en una granja de Tennessee, cubierto con sus propios jeans y los jeans del asesino.

programme.title: Crímenes imperfectos
programme.desc: El cuerpo de una atractiva joven fue encontrado a una milla de su auto abandonado.

programme.title: Crímenes imperfectos
programme.desc: En 1969, la operadora telefónica de 25 años Diane Maxwell es violada y asesinada. Su hermano le prometió que averiguaría quién fue el responsable y llevaría al asesino ante la justicia.

programme.title: Crímenes imperfectos
programme.desc: La escena del crimen fue especialmente violenta: un esposo y una esposa fueron asesinados a tiros en su habitación. ¿Fue cómplice su hija de 16 años?

programme.title: Crímenes imperfectos
programme.desc: Una peluquera joven y atractiva fue agredida sexualmente y asesinada en su propio salón de belleza. La evidencia en la escena del crimen no coincidió con ninguno de los sospechosos y, después de la investigación inicial, el caso se archivó por diez años.

programme.title: Crímenes imperfectos
programme.desc: Cuando dos mujeres desaparecieron y luego fueron encontradas brutalmente asesinadas, la policía se preguntó si fueron víctimas de un crimen de odio.

programme.title: Crímenes imperfectos
programme.desc: Se descubrió un esqueleto humano en las marismas de Carolina del Norte y, cuando los investigadores descubrieron que había estado muerta durante 18 meses, sabían que sería difícil descubrir quién era, y mucho más quién la mató.

programme.title: Crímenes imperfectos
programme.desc: Después de dispararle a sus víctimas en la cabeza, el asesino organizó la escena, colocó la evidencia incriminatoria en una bolsa de plástico y la arrojó al río.

programme.title: Narcos: Mexico
programme.desc: (S1E6) A violent power struggle erupts between Falcón and Rafa. As Félix finds a footing in the cocaine business, the DEA tries to lure him into the U.S.

programme.title: Narcos: Mexico
programme.desc: (S1E7) María implores Félix to move back to Sinaloa. Kiki gathers evidence of the Guadalajara cartel's pot fields. Neto Mourns.

programme.title: Narcos: Mexico
programme.desc: (S1E8) After the DEA closes in on Rafa's enormous pot field, Félix tries to stop his associates from retaliating. Kiki and Jaime meet with investigators.

programme.title: Narcos: Mexico
programme.desc: (S1E9) A desperate Jaime is stymied by bureaucratic paperwork. Mika worries about her husband. Félix urges Rafa to disappear.

programme.title: Narcos: Mexico
programme.desc: (S1E10) As pressure mounts, Félix returns to Sinaloa. An enraged Jaime and Mika seek justice and answers.

programme.title: Narcos
programme.desc: (S1E1) Chilean drug chemist Cockroach brings his product to Colombian smuggler Pablo Escobar. DEA agent Steve Murphy joins the war on drugs in Bogota.

programme.title: Narcos
programme.desc: (S1E2) Communist radical group M-19 makes a move against the narcos, while Murphy gets an education in Colombian law enforcement from his new partner Peña.

programme.title: Narcos
programme.desc: (S1E3) Murphy encounters the depths of government corruption when he and Peña try to derail Escobar's political ambitions by proving he's narco.

programme.title: Narcos
programme.desc: (S1E4) Despite a new extradition treaty, the U.S. puts more money into fighting communism, creating new challenges for Murphy and Peña in the hunt for Pablo.

programme.title: Narcos
programme.desc: (S1E5) Pablo's extreme methods put the narcos on the brink of war with Carillo and the government. Peña tries to protect his witness.

programme.title: Narcos
programme.desc: (S1E6) Peña and Carillo close in on Gacha. Murphy tries to protect pro-extradition candidate Gaviria from a notorious assassin connected to Pablo.

programme.title: Narcos
programme.desc: (S1E7) Pablo goes into hiding as the political tide turns against him, but he finds a way to strike back. Murphy and Peña finally get the CIA to help them.

programme.title: Narcos
programme.desc: (S1E8) A tragic mistake forces the government to change tactics in the fight against Pablo. But Pablo faces bigger threats from inside his empire.

programme.title: Narcos
programme.desc: (S1E9) The hunt for Pablo seems to be over after he makes a deal with the government, but Murphy and Peña - and the Cali Cartel - have other plans.

programme.title: Narcos
programme.desc: (S1E10) Pablo's activities in prison provoke the government into taking extreme action. Murphy and Peña face a situation of their own.

programme.title: Narcos
programme.desc: (S2E1) In the aftermath of a massive military effort to take Pablo into custody, the family reunites while enemies worry. Steve and Connie fight about safety.

programme.title: Narcos
programme.desc: (S1E10) Las actividades de Pablo desde la prisión hacen que el gobierno tome acciones extremas. Murphy y Peña se enfrentan a un problema diferente.

programme.title: Narcos
programme.desc: (S1E2) El grupo comunista radical M-19 se enfrenta a los narcos, mientras Peña le enseña a Murphy las reglas del juego de acuerdo con las leyes colombianas.

programme.title: Narcos
programme.desc: (S2E1) Después del fallido intento para capturar a Pablo, la familia se reune mientras sus enemigos se preocupan. Steve y Connie discuten sobre seguridad.

programme.title: Narcos
programme.desc: (S2E2) Tata está cansada de la vida de prófugos. Pablo reta al presidente Gaviria con una contraoferta por su captura. Steve y Javier conocen a su nuevo jefe.

programme.title: Narcos
programme.desc: (S2E3) El presidente Gaviria ofrece una nueva misión a un viejo conocido. La nueva estrategia de búsqueda implementada por el gobierno preocupa a Pablo, pero también acongoja a Steve y a Javier.

programme.title: Narcos
programme.desc: (S2E4) El Cartel de Cali hace planes para adueñarse del territorio de Pablo. Limón propone un plan a Maritza. Tata obtiene una pistola para su protección.

programme.title: Narcos
programme.desc: (S2E5) Hay un nuevo líder en el bloque de búsqueda. Javier ya no cree en el sistema. Pablo trae a Carlos de Miami para animar a Tata.

programme.title: Narcos
programme.desc: (S2E6) El recién formado Cartel de Los Pepes decide destruir a Pablo y a su Imperio. Carlos conseja a Tata que escape a un lugar seguro con sus hijos.

programme.title: Narcos
programme.desc: (S2E7) Ante el inminente peligro para los Escobar, Pablo envía su familia a otro país. Gaviria ve la oportunidad para usarlos como moneda de cambio.

programme.title: Narcos
programme.desc: (S2E8) Colombia le da la espalda a Escobar después de un ataque terrorista. Tata recibe ayuda de un aliado inesperado. Quica sufre de ansiedad.

programme.title: Narcos
programme.desc: (S2E9) Pablo se reune con un familiar lejano. La vida de July Moncada está en peligro. La DEA y la CIA no se ponen de acuerdo en una estrategia para enfrentar a Los Pepes.

programme.title: Narcos
programme.desc: (S2E10) Javier sufre las consecuencias por la entrevista de Judy. Tata intenta convencer a Pablo para que se rinda por el bien de los niños.

programme.title: Narcos
programme.desc: (S3E1) En una reunión del Cartel de Cali, los jefes hacen un anuncio inesperado sobre el futuro del negocio.

programme.title: Narcos
programme.desc: (S3E2) Jorge interviene para rescatar el acuerdo de cooperación entre el cartel de Cali y el gobierno después de un incidente. Peña tiene problemas con su contacto en los Pepes.

programme.title: Narcos
programme.desc: (S3E3) Los hermanos Rodríguez se esconden durante las negociaciones. Pacho conoce al Señor de los Cielos en México. El nuevo equipo de Peña en la DEA visita Cali.

programme.title: Narcos
programme.desc: (S3E4) Peña tiene un nuevo plan para capturar a Gilberto Rodríguez, líder del cartel de Cali. Amado propone un negocio a Pacho.

programme.title: Narcos
programme.desc: (S3E5) Paranoico ante posibles filtraciones, Miguel aumenta su seguridad. Pacho le da una respuesta a Amado. Peña busca testigos.
